# Deploy to Vercel after changes

Whenever you finish implementing or fixing something in this project (unless the user says not to):

1. Commit the relevant changes (ask first only if the user has not already asked to update Vercel / deploy).
2. `git push origin main` (or the current branch).
3. Redeploy production: `npx vercel --yes --prod`.
4. Tell the user the live URL: https://tourvego.vercel.app

Do this as part of completing the task — do not wait for a separate “deploy” request. The user expects Vercel to stay in sync with the latest work.
